Kind of off topic but.... Frank have you looked at the Ramsey signal magnet antenna. I bought one and use it for my SW receiver and it really reaches the stations in the noise. I wonder if you would be able to incorporate it into your system.

http://www.ramseyelectronics.com/cgi-bin/commerce.exe?preadd=action&key=SM100

Regards,

Frank R.

----- Original Message ----
From: purplespacefriend &lt;purplealiengirl@...&gt;
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Sent: Tuesday, April 22, 2008 9:11:36 AM
Subject: [EVP-ITC] Re: .....then why do I feel guilty?

                 well, I&#39;m still here. I try to more patient these days, and instead 
of arguing, I&#39;d rather just go do my own thing, and the ones 
claiming to be experts can have it. 

Even after making the boxes since 2002, I have no idea how or why 
it works, I only know if you do certain things, &quot;they&quot; talk. I don&#39;t 
do investigations, and still think there is no haunting if no one 
living is there to see/experience it. Spirit is pretty much 
infinately more sophistcated than most imagine. As far as I can 
tell, all limitations are on this side of the veil. 

I get a little irritated when I make the boxes, yet someone else is 
going to tell me how it really works, especially when they 
themselves have no technical knowledge on any level.

For me, I enjoy the challenge of getting this stuff to work, and 
the voices are a joy to hear, but almost secondary. I work alone, 
and don&#39;t need the group&#39;s approval, so when someone is claiming to 
be the atuhority on this stuff, I don&#39;t care, I can just as easily 
quit the group and work by myself, which is pretty much what I 
prefer anyway. 

Mass production doesn&#39;t seem to come together, like I think it 
would if it was supposed to be, so I don&#39;t think that&#39;s a direction 
I want to pursue. I try to just provide the informatiin on what I do 
so others can dupicate it when possible. 

Frank-S

